    "headline": "One Thing I'm Watching: Systematic Hedge Funds' $86 Billion Buying Spree",
    "summary": "Systematic hedge funds known as commodity trading advisors, or CTAs, bought $86 billion worth of global equities over the past five sessions, according to a note from Goldman Sachs sent to clients Thursday.  As I wrote last week, Goldman’s models were suggesting that CTAs were on the precipice of a massive buying spree as they closed out short positions and flipped long.  The last three times that CTAs have bought at such a level, stocks usually pulled back in the near term but did well over the following months.",
